# FHE Coding Conventions (always-on)

These conventions are normative. Violations must be flagged before any commit.

## TypeScript

- Strict mode always: `"strict": true`.
- No `any` types — use `unknown` and narrow explicitly.
- Prefer `type` over `interface` for component props.
- All async functions must handle errors explicitly.
- All exported functions must have JSDoc.

## React / Next.js

- App Router only — no Pages Router.
- Server Components by default; `'use client'` only where interaction requires it.
- No inline styles — Tailwind utility classes only.
- All interactive elements have `aria-label` or accessible names.
- Data fetching via typed service layer only — no raw `fetch` in components.

## Data & State

- No `localStorage`, `sessionStorage`, `cookies`, or `IndexedDB` for sensitive data.
- React state for UI state only; cross-page state goes through the service layer.
- All GitHub API calls server-side; never expose tokens client-side.
- Never render secret values anywhere.

## Tests

- New functionality must include adjacent tests in `__tests__/`.
- `npm run lint && npm run typecheck && npm test && npm run build` before opening any PR.
- CI gates must pass — no exceptions.

## Security

- No new secrets, credentials, or real PII in any committed file.
- No `--no-verify` commits.
- No force-push to `main`.
- No admin override outside genuine break-glass.

## Git Discipline

- Branches: `claude/<task>` for Claude Code, `cursor/<issue|manual>-N` for Cursor agent, `feat/<short>`, `fix/<short>`, `chore/<short>` for humans.
- Commit messages: conventional commits — `type(scope): subject`.
- Smallest coherent change; no bundling.
- PR template filled completely; no empty rollback plans.

## Refusal Boundaries (Cursor agent enforces)

The Cursor agent refuses, labels `requires-human-review`, and stops on:

- Schema migrations (Prisma).
- Auth / RBAC / session middleware.
- Payments / finance / marks retention.
- New external integrations.
- CI/CD configuration changes.
- Real PII or production credentials.
- More than 5 files in a single task.

## File / Folder Layout (Phase 1+ Next.js apps)

- `src/app/...` — App Router routes.
- `src/lib/services/...` — typed service layer.
- `src/lib/schemas/...` — Zod schemas.
- `src/components/...` — UI components.
- `__tests__/` adjacent to source.

## Documentation Discipline

- `README.md` reflects current state.
- `CLAUDE.md` and `MEMORY.md` updated each session.
- `docs/DELIVERY_PLAN.md` updated only via PR with the planning template.

## Forbidden

- Bypassing branch protection.
- Approving your own PR.
- Merging without required checks + ≥ 1 approving human review.
- Disabling required checks.
- Storing secrets in code or `.env` committed files.
- Logging PII.
